In addition, GBX is sometimes used (for example on the London Stock Exchange) to denote [[Penny sterling]], a subdivision of pound sterling, the currency for the United Kingdom.

===Cryptocurrencies===
Recently, [[cryptocurrency|cryptocurrencies]] have unofficially used ISO codes on various cryptocurrency exchanges, for instance LTC for [[Litecoin]], NMC for [[Namecoin]] and XRP for [[Ripple (payment protocol)|Ripple]]. [[SIX Interbank Clearing]] (a Maintenance Agency of ISO) is currently studying the impact and role of cryptocurrencies and other independent currencies on ISO 4217.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.six-interbank-clearing.com/dam/downloads/en/clearit/63-64/4217.pdf|title=SIX Interbank ISO 4217: A controversial standard|publisher=}}</ref>

